cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.DM, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper is focused on graph drawing research, which is a subfield of computational geometry.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the running time cost of force-directed algorithms and proposes a heuristic algorithm for speeding up the iteration.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as network graph drawing is often used in the analysis of social and information networks.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as graph theory is a subfield of discrete mathematics and the paper discusses the convergence of iteration sequence.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also possible as the paper proposes a numerical method (successive over-relaxation) for improving the performance of force-directed algorithms.
